race.description: Picklebet Get Your Pickle On Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: DIAMANTINA ROSE (7) has been close up in stronger Maidens and the speedy mare is well placed with the 3kg claim. She will skip across to the speed and will be hard to run down. SUTHERLAND (2) impressed beaten a nose in a 65 at Dalby over 1000m. She has won 2/2 at this track/distance and has an inside barrier and handy 2kg claim. Back in grade and a player. MINOR KEY (4) has been giving away starts but has his share of ability and plenty of scope for improvement. He had market support over 800m at Ipswich first-up and draws handy again. He can get some of the money if things go his way. CHAYSE'N'SCOTTY (5) resumed at the Gold Coast well-supported but didn't have much luck. He's been off the scene for 285 days and is sure to have come on. Drops back 200m, but he will get every chance from an inside barrier.
